  "prompt": "What was the universe before Big Bang?",
  "response": "The nature of the universe before the Big Bang is a topic of considerable speculation and debate among scientists, as there is currently no definitive evidence to describe conditions preceding the Big Bang. The prevailing theory is that the Big Bang marks the beginning of time and space as we understand it, meaning there may not be a \"before\" in any conventional sense.\n\nSeveral hypotheses have been proposed to explain what might have existed before the Big Bang:\n\n1. **Quantum Fluctuations**: Some theories suggest that the universe could have originated from quantum fluctuations in a vacuum. According to this idea, the universe was in a quantum state before the Big Bang.\n\n2. **Cosmic Cycles**: Another hypothesis posits that the universe goes through infinite cycles of expansion and contraction, known as the \"cyclic model\" or \"oscillatory universe.\" In this scenario, the Big Bang would be just one phase in an eternal cycle.\n\n3. **Multiverse Theory**: Some physicists propose that our universe is just one of many in a larger multiverse. Before the Big Bang, our universe might have been part of a larger multiverse structure with different physical laws and conditions.\n\n4. **Pre-Big Bang State**: There are also theories suggesting a pre-Big Bang state governed by different physical laws than those we currently understand. This state could involve higher dimensions or a different form of matter and energy.\n\nUltimately, these ideas are speculative and based on theoretical models. Observational evidence is limited, and the true nature of the universe before the Big Bang remains one of the most profound mysteries in cosmology.",
